{
  "texts": [
    "We then predict the click probabilities for the entire set S consisting of both positive and negative samples.",
    "To compute the prediction error, we adopt the pseudorank score as proposed in (Qi et al. 2022).",
    "The pseudo-rank score for each instance is defined as:",
    "The final NCE loss is computed as the cross-entropy loss over the pseudo-rank scores for all training instances in set S:",
    "where S is the set of the positive training samples."
  ]
}